---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1%unit}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Halve, core, and thinly slice @Granny Smith apple{1%unit}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced). Roughly chop @walnuts{1/2%ounce}(roughly chopped).

In a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @pepper{to taste}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until shallot is softened, ~{30-50%seconds}. Set aside until ready to use in next step.

Melt @butter{1/2%tbsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add @dried thyme{1/4%tsp} and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. (Save remaining thyme for another use.)

Add apple, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Let apple cool slightly, then transfer to bowl with pickled shallot. Toss to combine. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%ounce} and walnuts; cook, stirring, until panko is golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on the panko—it browns quickly!

Transfer to a small #bowl{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

In a large bowl, toss together @arugula{2%ounce}, @mixed greens{2%ounce}, @blue cheese dressing{1.5%ounce}, half the apple and pickled shallot (draining first), half the walnut panko, and half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide salad between shallow #bowls{}. Top with remaining apple and pickled shallot, remaining walnut panko, and remaining feta. Serve.